How do you want to solve this problem?
When, as a citizen, I lobbied for the purpose of guiding tourism activities as a liberal profession, I was successful.
The problem is politics: when someone arrives from the left or the right with a good project, it is knowingly refused and it delays the citizens.
As an independent member of no party, I have a much greater chance of gaining the support of all the parliamentary parties.
I have the advantage of being able, without partisan categorization and dogma, to take from each side what is best for our country and implement it.
Do you consider yourself a man of the right or the left?
From a Czech point of view, I feel like people are putting me on the left.
For me, whether it's a little left or right, it's not really important.
For me, the important thing is that we are moving forward.
What matters to me is not that people are left-wing or right-wing, but to bring people together.
I always support any solution contributing to the common good, even if it is proposed by the Communist Party or ODS and I act equally impartially against bad ideas.
Do you enrage when someone says you are a populist?
But doesn't what you said prove it?
When you develop a business plan in a company, you also have a certain optimal purpose and vision.
You're trying to get closer.
Some may call it populism, but all the proposals I’m talking about have been applied by the world and recognized experts have talked about it.
But without the support of the parliament, you only have slogans.
You won’t survive long in politics with that.
Do you think that if you go to people and talk to them, you will succeed, for example, in imposing material and criminal responsibility?
I have no other option.
I have to convince politicians, journalists and public opinion and try to rally them to my camp in order to impose it.
If I were elected president, it would not be a problem to broadcast live on television my request to the presidents of the parliamentary parties to legislate on the material and criminal responsibility of politicians, officials, judges and prosecutors.
They should then explain why they do not want it.
When there is a strong personality who will identify abuse, it will be possible to put pressure on the political scene.
Take, for example, the election of the president by direct suffrage, it was obtained thanks to the pressure of public opinion.
I admit, without ambages, to be an amateur, not a genius or an intellectual.
I'm trying to find allies for my opinions and visions.
I have just started politics and I am trying to get the majority support for my program.
I'm trying, alone, to move things forward, and if it doesn't work, I'll stop in six years and go back to the private sector.
It's like Okamura is supposed to save the Czech Republic.
I'm not a savior.
I know that one person cannot make a difference, which is why I went to see a number of personalities to ask them to run in the Senate elections as well.
I met Radim Jančura, but he refused because of the amount of work.
I at least supported investigative journalist Jana Lorenová who revealed the oil fraud.
I introduced myself because people are really unhappy but now I hesitate.
Sixty percent of people did not vote and what did, for the most part, gave their voice to an establishment representative.
In the Senate, we are only two independents.
People have elected a Senate that can hardly impose changes.
Nevertheless, I will fight for my vision, for example the direct election of mayors and prefects of regions.
Are you planning to start your own party?
No, not yet, because I do not have time to check if the past of each potential member is spotless and then I do not have the financial means.
I also have no money for my presidential campaign, I only have twenty thousand in my "transparent" account.
You don't have money?
You're talking about tax returns, what's yours?
